Casting Call!

Non-union project looking for male actor for a short thriller. Festival bound project.

Shooting: 1/31 and 2/7 in Los Angeles.

Age range: 35-55

Dominic is a complex character, embodying the qualities of a manipulative loner. He lures young and unsuspecting women, using his persuasive abilities to get what he wants.

Compensation: Copy, credit, meals and transportation.

Involves intimacy: kissing

If interested, email casting@jbgimagination.com

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

items.text:
Casting Call (Non-Union) for ALL AGES, ALL DEMOGRAPHICS - Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of a client in a simulated therapy session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. The sessions include some scripted elements to prepare, and then some improv with prompts.

All ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are welcome. 

All experience levels with acting are welcome. We are committed to making this a respectful and safe process, with open communication and respect for boundaries.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are January 22 to February 6, based on actor availability, but our needs are ongoing and more will occur in the future, so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is $60 CAD per hour, with the expectation of some prepared material, studio session duration: 1-2 hours. If there is some significant preparation required, compensation is offered for that time.

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume, as well as some information about you, such as gender identity, age, cultural/racial background. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again. We do sometimes receive more submissions than we are able to respond to, but we do read them all, and we do save your submissions for future consideration.

items.text:
EXCITING NEWS!

I'm thrilled to share my screenplay/book EDDIE'S BACK - A gripping story that I believe would make a FANTASTIC MOVIE. 

I have already WRITTEN AND COPYRIGHTED THE SCREENPLAY, so it's ready to go! Now I'm reaching out to PRODUCTION COMPANIES , LITERARY AGENTS , FILM AGENTS AND #DIRECTORS who might be interested in bringing this story to life on the big screen.

EDDIE'S BACK - May 1963, Eddie a popular teenager is intentionally hit by a car, which leaves him in a coma. It's 2026, Eddie wakes up. He is shocked and disappointed at what he sees. Until the ghost of JFK visits him and INSPIRES HIM to make a difference.

Now Eddie 79 years young, realizes why he was KEPT ALIVE and what he has to do.

However, a senior Senator with an agenda of his own is watching Eddie's every move and is prepared to stop Eddie's mission at any cost.

DREAM CAST (just imagining!)

#HarrisonFord - #CandyClark - #PaulLeMat - #RichardDreyfuss - #CharlesMartinSmith - #BradleyCooper -#MatthewMcConaughey - #MargotRobbie - #TaylorSwift - #AnneHathaway - #ParisHilton - #JordonHudson - #LaurenSanchez - #AmberHeard - #KrisJenner  #SydneySweeney - #TinaLouise - #CarolBurnett - #ColinHanks - #SenatorJohnKennedy 

DIRECTOR - #RonHoward 

NO OFFICIAL TIES - JUST PUTTING IT OUT THERE AND HOPING TO GET EDDIE'S BACK - INTO THE RIGHT HANDS!

TAGGING TOP AGENCIES: 

@ImageEntertainment - @IndependentArtistGroup - #WilliamMorrisEndeavor - #VerveTalentandLiteraryManagement - #CreativeArtistsAgency - #TheWayneAgency. And Indie powerhouses like: #A24 - #AnnapurnalPictures - #PlanBEntertainment - #BlumHouseProductions - #KillerFilms - #Neon - #FilmNation - #BleeckerStreet - #ElaraPictures - #BigBeach - #APAAgency - #UnitedTalentAgency - #GershAgency - #ArtistsFirst - #IFCFilms - #SonyClassics - #LionsGate 

NO OFFICIAL TIES - Just putting it out there and hoping to get - EDDIE'S BACK into THE RIGHT HANDS!

PRODUCTION COMPANIES I ADMIRE:

#SONYPICTURES - #WARNERBROSDISCOVERY - #IMAGEENTERTAINMENT - #WALTDISNEYPICTURES - #HelloSunshine - #BadRobot - #FifthSeason 

PRODUCERS - I'd love to work with:

#MarkCiardi - #MattDamon - #MarkWahlberg #WillFerrell - #TomHanks - #JeffBezos - #ElonMusk - #ChristineVachon - #TeddySchwarzman - #NinaYangBongiovi #LenaWaithe 

NO OFFICIAL TIES - JUST PUTTING IT OUT THERE. HOPING TO GET (EDDIE'S BACK) INTO THE RIGHT HANDS.

I'd also like to catch the eye of DIRECTORS like: #StevenSpielberg - #RonHoward - #StevenSoderbergh - #ToscaMusk - #RyleeScott - #SofiaCoppola - #GeorgeLucas - #BenStiller 

Their storytelling I admire deeply.

No Official ties - Just hoping to catch the eye of these incredible teams.

If you know someone in the film or media who might love this concept, please feel free to REACH OUT or SHARE THIS POST. 

IMDB.ME  https://pro.imdb.com/name/nm4381966

LET'S MAKE MOVIE MAGIC HAPPEN!

#EDDIE'S BACK #BooktoFilm #Screenplayready #FilmAdaptation #Moviepitch #Filmmakers #Independantfilm #IndieCinema #literaryagents

We are looking for a Fight Choreographer for our fan film For Becoming Our Spider-Man, a Miles Moralesâ€“centered action project.

The film features a major, high-energy action sequence where Miles initially clashes with Hobgoblin (Uncle Aaron) â€” before the two of them ultimately team up to take down larger threats: Shocker and Beetle (Janice Lincoln). This creates a chaotic, fast-paced, and emotionally charged battle that we want to feel cinematic and professional.
You would help choreograph: Rooftop combat between Miles and Hobgoblin that evolves into a partnership.

A dramatic crash through a stained-glass window into a criminal hideout.
Fast, acrobatic Spider-Man-style movement.
A two-versus-two fight as Miles and Hobgoblin take on Shocker and Beetle.
Action moments involving Milesâ€™s invisibility and bioelectric â€œVenomâ€ powers.
Weâ€™re looking for someone who can:
Create clear, exciting, and visually dynamic fight choreography.
Work patiently with young performers.

Prioritize safety while keeping the action intense and believable.

Attend rehearsals on January 22nd, January 25th, and February 9th, ahead of our main shoot on February 11th. 

The location will be in aveley park in Essex 

Experience in martial arts, stage combat, or stunt work is preferred â€” but passion for action filmmaking matters most.
If youâ€™re interested, please message me via email: ppeterb954@gmail.com please and thank you

items.text:
We are now casting our Spring show Shake Rattle And Roll and looking for self Contained experienced hardworking performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community .The 
The show is a celebration to all the greatest songs and stars of the 50s 60s 70s The Beatles ,Elvis, Doris Day, Connie Francis ,Cliff Richard, Buddy Holly and more.
Dates
Rehearsals- 23rd -27th February 
Playing Dates- 2nd March  -1st  May 
We work Monday to Friday (2 x 60 minute shows per day) 
Casting Breakdown We are now looking for strong /experienced Male and Female singer /performers 
The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced performers that can hold an audience and are looking for engaging vocalist performers.
We are looking for drivers with cars only .
We are looking for performers on all area of the UK -please include bases when sending details.
We are offering 700 per week plus fuel on the road 
Please send details including a singing reel to info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

# **Casting Call â€“ Vancouver Laser & Skin Care Centre**

Hi everyone!
We are currently casting talent for **vertical ads **to promote our upcoming **February & March campaign**.

## **Roles Needed**
* **2 talents (male & female)**
* **Age:** 25â€“35
* **Ethnicity:** Caucasian or East Asian
* **Language:** Native-level English fluency
* **Preferred (not required):** Experience with social media content, beauty industry, or ad shoots

##  **Project Details**
* **Deliverables:** 6â€“9 vertical videos (approx. 15-second ads)
* **Shoot Duration:** 3.5â€“4 hours (approx.)
* **Shoot Date:** 
For the **February Shooting**: One day between **January 21-23** (exact date TBC)
For the **March Shooting**: One day between **February 16-25** (exact date TBC)
* **Location**: 750 W Broadway 3rd Floor, Vancouver, BC V5Z 1H2
* **Wardrobe & Makeup:** Not provided â€” please dress in **business-casual style**

##  **Compensation**
* **$300 flat rate**
* **One BBL or PicoWay Treatment**
* **Snacks & coffee provided** 

## **How to Apply**

Please email the following to **ben@vancouverlaser.com**
**Subject line:** *February/March Campaign + [Your Name]*
* Headshot
* Resume
* Demo videos (if available)

**Please note that private messages will not be replied to**.

If you have any questions, feel free to reach out.
We look forward to your submissions!

items.text:
**CASTING CALL â€“ AMBER (LEAD ROLE)**

**Short Film | Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller**

Hello everyone,

Weâ€™re reopening casting for the **lead role of Amber** due to an unexpected last-minute change. The actress previously cast had to step away for a paid commitment. There are no hard feelings â€” we completely understand and wish her the best. This does, however, mean weâ€™re reaching out again in hopes of finding the right person to step in and collaborate with us.
**PROJECT DETAILS**

**Project:** Short Film
**Genre:** Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller
**Shoot Location:** Lower Mainland, BC
**Shoot Date:** **Sunday, January 18th**
**Compensation:** Volunteer / Passion Project

All preparation is already in place. If youâ€™re available and able to step in, you would genuinely be **saving the day** and helping us keep the shoot on track.
**ROLE: AMBER**

**Age Range:** 27â€“40
**Gender:** Female
**Ethnicity:** Open / Race-agnostic
**CHARACTER SNAPSHOT**

Amber is a high-performing Director of Sales at a tech company. Outwardly confident and disciplined, she is internally restless and unable to feel content. She is addicted to the chaseâ€”always moving forward, never celebrating wins.

When Amber gains access to an experimental technology, she begins to rely on it too heavily. The technology destabilizes her judgment, blurring truth, error, and perception.

By the end, she withdraws from modern lifeâ€”not in rebellion, but to preserve her sanity.
**PERFORMANCE NOTES**

This is a **subtle, internal performance**. We are seeking an actor who can convey psychological shifts through restraint, stillness, and micro-expression.

This is not a loud breakdown. Amberâ€™s collapse is quiet, logical, and unsettlingâ€”driven by over-certainty and a loss of trust in her own judgment.
**KEY TRAITS**
* Intelligent
* Controlled
* Ambitious (not arrogant)
* Emotionally guarded
* Increasingly detached
**AUDITION / SUBMISSION**

Self-tape audition
One dramatic scene (sides will be provided)

Please submit:
* Headshot
* Resume (if available)

**Email:** soultales.ca@gmail.com
**Subject:** AMBER â€“ Casting Submission

items.text:
***FREE SOLO SHOW CLASS THIS SATURDAY ***

Hello Acting Community!

Are you curious about creating a ONE PERSON SHOW?

Then you do not want to miss this 100% FREE, 100% AWESOME solo theatre class "The Art of Creating the One Person Show" commencing THIS SAT JANUARY 17th @10AM (PST)/12pm (CST)/1pm (EST) via Zoom.

RSVP HERE: [https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/](https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/)

I have been teaching this ongoing FREE class for over a decade and I have been working in the genre of Solo Theatre for over 20 years. I have directed & developed well over 175 solo shows and toured successfully with my own award-winning solo shows, and I would be honored and excited to help guide YOU into your own success as a Solo Artist.

**ALL EXPERIENCE LEVELS WELCOME**, and no material needed to bring to the virtual class as I always provide a writing prompt. If you do have a solo excerpt you wish to share, that option will be available too.

All you need to attend this Zoom class is a willingness to explore, something to write with and on, and an RSVP here: [https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/](https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/)

I truly hope you will join the Soaring Solo Community and I for this fabulous virtual event. Let's turn your solo show dreams into an amazing reality!

Jessica

Founder & CEO of Soaring Solo Studios

Blogger for NoHo Arts

Director/Teaching Artist for the LA Women's Theatre Festival

Director & Developer of over 175 solo shows

ATTENTION CENTRAL FL ACTORS 

SHOOT OPPORTUNITY; ONE DAY ONLY

M. 50â€™s-70â€™s, Sheriff Role Available for Improv Comedy Short Film.  

*Chief Harris is a small town bumbling sheriff who loves pancakes and isn't that great at his job. He's very southern, and means well. In this short film, Chief Harris is sitting down with a documentary crew to tell the story of a series of serial murders that occurred 20 years ago.*

Submit your headshot to comesaroundmovie@gmail.com to receive more info. 

Signup with our Calendly link for a virtual audition! [https://calendly.com/comesaroundmovie/30min](https://calendly.com/comesaroundmovie/30min) 

Shooting will occur in Lakeland Fl, on January 24th 2026 from 9am-4:30pm.

Talent will receive up to $25 in travel cost reimbursement.

items.text:
GODSPELL â€” VIDEO AUDITIONS

Wedgwood Arts

Wedgwood Arts is pleased to announce video auditions for Godspell! This non-paid production will be joyful, ensemble-driven, and thoughtfully crafted. We are seeking performers who value storytelling, collaboration, and making meaningful theatre together.

The Production team for Godspell:
Director: A. Solomon Abah Jr.
Music Direction: Adam Frame
Choreographer: (TBA) 
Stage Manager: (TBA)

PERFORMANCE DATES

April 17â€“19

AUDITION SUBMISSION DETAILS

Audition Deadline: Saturday, February 7 at 11:59pm
Callbacks: Monday, February 9 at St. Matthewâ€™s Lutheran Church
 5709 Wedgwood Dr. Fort Worth, TX. 76133

Where to Send Auditions
wedgwoodarts@gmail.com

Email Subject Line
Godspell Audition â€“ [Your Name]

WHAT TO SUBMIT
1. Vocal Selection

â€¢ One song, 60â€“90 seconds
â€¢ Musical theatre or contemporary style preferred
â€¢ Focus on clear text, musical accuracy, and connection
â€¢ Recorded accompaniment, live accompaniment, or a cappella are all acceptable
â€¢ Singing from Godspell is welcome but not required

2. Audition Side
The following Audition side has 3 parts a Narrot, a father, and a son. Have fun and show us different choices for each voice. We are excited to see your personality, sincerity, and ease with an audience.:

The son ran to meet his father, threw his arms around him, and kissed him, saying: â€œFather, I have sinned against God and against you; I am no longer fit to be called your son; treat me as one of your paid servants.â€ But the father called to one of his servants: â€œQuick, fetch me my robe, my best one. Put a ring on his finger and shoes on his feet and bring the fatted calf and kill it. And let us have a feast to celebrate the day, for this son of mine was lost and is found.â€ And the festivities began!

3. Movement

â€¢ 20â€“30 seconds of simple movement
â€¢ Movement to music or light choreography is welcome
â€¢ No dance experience requiredâ€”comfort, rhythm, and willingness to move are what matter most

4. Slate (At the Beginning of Your Video)

Please include:
â€¢ Your name
â€¢ Pronouns (optional)
â€¢ Age range
â€¢ Vocal range (if known)
â€¢ Any instruments you play (if applicable)

5. Video Guidelines

â€¢ One video or multiple videos are fine
â€¢ Phone recordings are perfectly acceptable
â€¢ Neutral background and good lighting recommended
â€¢ Please record each section in one continuous take

6. IN THE EMAIL BODY

First and last name 
Phone number 
Email 
Which parts you are willing to accept 
Any rehearsal conflicts 

REHEARSAL COMMITMENT

Rehearsals begin Monday, February 16 and will be held on Monday and Thursday nights from 7:00â€“10:00 PM and Saturdays from 10:00-1:00. 

This process will move intentionally and efficiently from the start, allowing us to create a polished, cohesive production while still building strong ensemble connections. Consistent attendance, preparation, and collaboration are essential.

Tech Week: April 12â€“14
Dress Rehearsal: April 16
Performances: April 17â€“19

Please audition only if you are able to commit to this schedule.

Godspell is a show rooted in generosity, joy, and shared responsibility. We are eager to bring together a company excited to do focused, meaningful work.

We look forward to seeing your auditions.

ROLES
We are looking for a diverse cast for this show. Performers of any ethnicity, race, color, sex, gender, age, sexual orientation, religion will be considered for the show. 
Jesus: The spiritual and emotional center of the piece. Warm, charismatic, and deeply grounded, with the ability to lead the ensemble through storytelling rather than authority. Strong singer with a gentle, confident presence. 
John the Baptist/Judas: A dual role. John the Baptist opens the show with joyful energy and clarity; Judas evolves into a conflicted, questioning figure. Requires emotional depth, strong acting skills, and vocal diversity. 
We are looking for 8 Actors who fill the following descriptions 
Performer 1: Energetic, playful, and physically expressive. Often drives movement-based storytelling and comic moments. Strong ensemble singer with confidence in unaccompanied sections. 
Performer 2: Bold, charismatic, and impulsive. Often delivers comedic text with sharp timing and physicality. Strong pop/rock vocal presence. 
Performer 3: Thoughtful, gentle, and reflective. Often anchors quieter moments and parables. Warm vocal tone and emotional sincerity. 
Performer 4: Expressive and emotionally open. Often carries lyrical and heartfelt material. Strong singer with the ability to communicate vulnerability. 
Performer 5: Bright, optimistic, and sincere. Frequently leads joyful or playful moments in the ensemble. Clear tone and strong blend. 
Performer 6: Quirky, imaginative, and playful. Comfortable with character work, storytelling, and musical humor. 
Performer 7: Grounded, mature, and emotionally resonant. Often supports dramatic moments with calm authority. Strong musicianship required. 
Performer 8: Confident, dynamic, and expressive. Often takes leadership within group numbers and physical storytelling. Strong rhythmic feel and vocal power.

John the Baptist/Judas: A dual role. John the Baptist opens the show with joyful energy and clarity; Judas evolves into a conflicted, questioning figure. Requires emotional depth, strong acting skills, and vocal diversity. 
We are looking for 8 Actors who fill the following descriptions 
Performer 1: Energetic, playful, and physically expressive. Often drives movement-based storytelling and comic moments. Strong ensemble singer with confidence in unaccompanied sections. 
Performer 2: Bold, charismatic, and impulsive. Often delivers comedic text with sharp timing and physicality. Strong pop/rock vocal presence. 
Performer 3: Thoughtful, gentle, and reflective. Often anchors quieter moments and parables. Warm vocal tone and emotional sincerity. 
Performer 4: Expressive and emotionally open. Often carries lyrical and heartfelt material. Strong singer with the ability to communicate vulnerability. 
Performer 5: Bright, optimistic, and sincere. Frequently leads joyful or playful moments in the ensemble. Clear tone and strong blend. 
Performer 6: Quirky, imaginative, and playful. Comfortable with character work, storytelling, and musical humor. 
Performer 7: Grounded, mature, and emotionally resonant. Often supports dramatic moments with calm authority. Strong musicianship required. 
Performer 8: Confident, dynamic, and expressive. Often takes leadership within group numbers and physical storytelling. Strong rhythmic feel and vocal power.

CASTING CALL - Short Dark Comedy/Noir
â€¢ Title: "Murder, No Rush"
â€¢ Type: Short
â€¢ Location: Boulder, CO
â€¢ Compensation: $50 (negotiable), lunch provided
â€¢ Time Commitment: 2 half-days (3-5 hours)

SYNOPSIS
Vivian, a vain housewife, conspires to kill her wealthy husband by hiring a hitman- but unbeknownst to her, the cops know exactly what she's up to.

ROLES:

â€¢ The Contractor: Male, 28-45+
A contract killer. Stoic, calculating, and cold-blooded; or at least that how he seems. Unknown to his client, he is secretly working for the police, undercover as a hitman.

â€¢ Detective Moss: Female, 30s+
An interrogator who knows how to get a confession without raising her voice. But she doesn't just want to prove guilt: she wants to know why.

TO SUBMIT:
â€¢ A headshot OR previous work OR request sides, record an audition.
â€¢ Subject Line: "[Your Name] - Murder, No Rush" 

If you're interested, please feel free to DM me directly here or email AydanMetsch@gmail.com. Script available upon request!

items.text:
CASTING CALL - Diaspora

We are casting for a short narrative film titled Diaspora, being developed and produced as part of our final year of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol.

Diaspora is set in 1970s Britain and follows a newly migrated Cypriot man applying for a British passport, whose encounter with a Balkan-born photographer leads both men to confront memories of displacement, identity, and belonging. Set largely within a photography studio, the film is intimate and character-driven, relying on subtle performance, quiet tension, and emotional restraint.

This is an intimate short film exploring displacement, identity in transition, and the unspoken grief carried by those who leave their homeland. 

Filming will take place in Bristol and surrounding areas in early March (exact dates TBC). This is a student production, unpaid, with travel expenses and food provided. The film is intended for university assessment, portfolio use, and festival submission.

We are casting Enemy Soldiers and Civilians for an intense, large-scale Field Hospital sequence in a war-time drama short film.

ğŸ“… January 24â€“25 (primarily Sunday, January 25)
ğŸ“ Big Dalton, Glendora

The film follows a teenage girl forced into adulthood while trying to survive in the midst of war. This Field Hospital scene is a major turning point: civilians gather at night believing they are safe, when a sudden enemy attack erupts and everything collapses into chaos.

We are looking for as many people as possible to create a crowded, immersive environment. This is a physically active, emotionally intense scene involving movement, urgency, and controlled chaos.

Details:

 â€¢ Seeking White / European actors

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

items.text:
Hey everyone!

We are now casting **non-union actors** for *An Empty Cup*, a satirical dramedy student short film supported by Vancouver Film School.

This is a **student-led, non-union volunteer production**. While unpaid, the project includes full craft services, catering, and a complimentary professional headshot session for selected performers.

Self-tape submissions open **January 14 at 9:00 AM** and close **January 24 at 11:00 PM**. In-person callbacks will be held on **January 26 from 12:00 PM to 4:00 PM**.

Filming is scheduled for **February 7â€“8, 2026** in the **Greater Vancouver Area**.

We are seeking talent for multiple roles with **open ethnicity casting** and encourage performers of all backgrounds to submit. Below, the synopsis of the film and roles of each character are posted.

For more information, please visit our Instagram (@anemptycup_film) or email us at anemptycupfilm@gmail.com.

-An Empty Cup Crew

sharedPost.text:
Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

items.text:
Wanted: 2 actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays.

We are looking for two versatile actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays: â€œThe Balled of Crooked Laneâ€ by Tom Mclennan and â€œWakeâ€ by Day Sheehan, to be performed on Wed 25th February (the awards evening) at the Gladstone Theatre, Port Sunlight. Both play were part of the Liverpool Fringe and won numerous nominations for best play etc.

Plays and parts descriptions.
â€œThe Ballad of Crooked Laneâ€ is set on the day Edward Rushton, prominent anti-slavery campaigner and blind poet, now well into middle age, awaits eye surgery to regain his sight. While waiting, he goes over his eventful life with his friend and biographer, William Shepherd, the Minister of Gateacre Chapel.

The part: The actor would play Billy the Ballad-monger in one important scene, a lively, upfront character full of humour, a seller of broadside ballads and casual acquaintance of Rushton. The actor would also fulfil several other small roles and be fully active on stage in what is an ensemble production.

â€œWakeâ€ When Daniel Anderson finds himself in an unfamiliar place with fragments of the previous night missing from his memory, he must piece together the truth of what happened. This experimental drama explores themes of guilt, responsibility, and the price of self-deception in a world where nothing is quite what it seems.

The part: POLICE OFFICER 2 (Any gender, 30s+) - The psychological manipulator who probes emotional wounds. The actor needs to be versatile as this role requires them to be multi faceted

No particular age or even gender is necessarily required We are looking for  actors who can bring the characters to life.

Audition date: Monday 26th January 7pm. Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA

Contact info@valleytheatre.co.uk or turn up on the night. No prep needed. audition will consist of short extract from the script.

Please note: There is no fee for these roles. Hopefully the material and occasion will appeal.
